### DABCUP ###

### Version ###
0.1

### What is it? ###
Dabcup is a program to simplify database backups and restoring. The goal is to
have one tool to manage several types of database with several types of storage.

### Supported storages ###
    - S3 (Amazon Simple Storage Service)
    - FTP
    - SFTP
    - LOCAL (local file system)

### Supported databases ###
    - PostgreSQL
    - MySQL

### Simple to use ###
dabcup.rb mysite.com store                # Stores your database
dabcup.rb mysite.com restore <name>       # Restores you database from a backup
dabcup.rb mysite.com clean                # Deletes old backups as specified in ~/.dabcup/.profiles.yml
dabcup.rb myblog.com list                 # Lists all backups available
dabcup.rb myblog.com delete <name>        # Deletes a backup

### Profiles ###
The list of databases to backup and storage informations are defined in
 ~/.dabcup/profiles.yml. The sample file is well documented and easily understanding.

### Required libraries ###
If you store your backup via Amazon S3 or SFTP you will need aws-s3 or net-ssh.
You can install easily these libraries with gem:
gem install aws-s3
gem install net-ssh